<h2 id="professional-overview">Professional Overview</h2>

<p>I am <strong>Dr. Zhanglong Cao</strong>, a statistician and biometrician specializing in advanced statistical methods for agricultural applications. Currently working as a Research Fellow in the Curtin Biometry and Agricultural Data Analytics (CBADA) team, I focus on developing and applying cutting-edge statistical methodologies to solve real-world challenges in agricultural science.</p>

<h2 id="research-expertise">Research Expertise</h2>

<p>My research encompasses a wide range of statistical methodologies:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>üìä Linear Mixed Models (LMM)</strong> - Advanced modeling for complex agricultural data</li>
  <li><strong>üîç Bayesian Statistics</strong> - Probabilistic inference and uncertainty quantification</li>
  <li><strong>üîÑ Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC)</strong> - Computational methods for complex models</li>
  <li><strong>üß™ Experimental Design</strong> - Optimal design strategies for agricultural trials</li>
  <li><strong>üåç Geostatistics</strong> - Spatial analysis and modeling</li>
  <li><strong>üìà Smoothing Splines</strong> - Non-parametric regression techniques</li>
  <li><strong>üåæ Applied Statistics in Agriculture</strong> - Real-world applications in crop science</li>
  <li><strong>üöú On-Farm Experiments</strong> - Field trial design and analysis</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="current-role--impact">Current Role &amp; Impact</h2>

<p>I lead statistical design and analysis for over <strong>50 GRDC-funded and industry-partnered projects</strong> (total value &gt;$43 Million), delivering high-impact research outputs including:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Peer-reviewed publications in top-tier journals</li>
  <li>R packages and decision-support tools</li>
  <li>Scalable frameworks embedded in national agricultural programs</li>
  <li>Interactive Shiny applications for data visualization</li>
</ul>

